  "prompt": "How is European hair different from African hair?",
  "response": "There are some notable differences between European and African hair types:\n\n1. Hair Structure\n- European hair tends to be straighter and thinner\n- African hair is typically more tightly coiled and has a more oval/flat cross-section\n- African hair is often more fragile and prone to breakage\n\n2. Hair Density\n- African hair generally has fewer hair follicles per square inch\n- European hair usually has more hair follicles and appears denser\n\n3. Growth Rate\n- African hair typically grows slower (about 0.9 cm per month)\n- European hair grows faster (about 1.2 cm per month)\n\n4. Moisture Retention\n- African hair is naturally drier due to its curl pattern\n- European hair tends to be more naturally oily\n\n5. Curl Pattern\n- African hair ranges from tight coils to kinky textures\n- European hair is usually straight or wavy\n\nThese differences are genetic and relate to evolutionary adaptations to different environmental conditions. It's important to note that individual variation exists, and these are general characteristics.",
